Acknowledgements

  1. You'll be recorded on video while answering questions and/or coding. Please do your best to look presentable as if you were taking an interview in person.
  2. You will need to record audio along with video. Please find a quiet place to take this interview where you can be heard clearly.
  3. While doing the code or data science challenge, Filtered will take screenshots of your work, record with your camera, and track the titles of tabs that you open. Please keep this in mind as you work.
  4. Filtered requires some personally-identifiable information (name, email, social media, etc.) in order to complete this interview. This information may or may not be shown to reviewers.

wifi
Network latency:
check_circlePassed
  • Consider disabling Adblock or similar browser plugin and then reload the page.
  • Consider connecting to a VPN service.
  • Consider connecting to the internet from a different location.
  • Consider closing all other programs that need access to the internet.
mic
Sound Input:
check_circlePassed
  • Please click the icon next to the address bar in your browser to verify or modify the audio permissions. (Reload the page to apply changes.)
  • If your room is very quiet, first make some sound to verify the status.
  • Try fully closing and restarting your browser or computer.
  • Try choosing different sound input sources from the dropdown.
  • Try changing your operating system settings to enable a microphone.
  • Please troubleshoot WebRTC on this site (opens in a new tab).
volume_up
Sound Output:
check_circlePassed
  • Please click the icon next to the address bar in your browser to verify or modify the audio permissions. (Reload the page to apply changes.)
  • Try choosing different sound output sources from the dropdown.
  • Try changing your operating system settings to enable an output device.
  • Please troubleshoot WebRTC on this site (opens in a new tab).
photo_camera
Camera:
check_circlePassed
  • Please click the icon next to the address bar in your browser to verify or modify the camera permissions. (Reload the page to apply changes.)
  • Check your browser settings to verify that hardware access can be given to Filtered.
  • Try choosing different camera input sources from the dropdown.
  • Try fully closing and restarting your browser or computer.
  • Try changing your operating system settings to enable a camera.
  • Please troubleshoot WebRTC on this site (opens in a new tab).
file_upload
File Upload:
check_circlePassed
  • If you're using the internet at the office or on a company computer, a firewall or proxy may be blocking your ability to upload. Please connect to a different internet network or consider using a personal computer.
